<article>
    <h1>Soft-Shell Crab with Almond Flakes ($19.80)</h1>
    <h2></h2>
    <section>
        <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/textview" title="The Straits Times">The Straits Times</a>
        - <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/20200830/textview" title="The Straits Times - 2020-08-30"><time>2020-08-30</time></a>
        - <span>LIFE FOOD &amp; DRINK</span>
        - <span role="byline"></span>
    </section>

    <p>Be­cause restau­rants here of­ten use frozen soft-shell crabs, the crus­taceans usu­ally turn out dry.</p>
    <p>Not these. Deep-fried till golden and crispy on the out­side, they boast moist and sweet flesh un­der­neath, as good as the live ones I have eaten in Viet­nam.</p>
    <p>The almond flakes match the crabs’ crisp­ness and add a nutty aroma. This dish re­minds me of the more com­mon ce­real prawns, but takes it up a notch.</p>

